{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-tipping-content-js","path":"/india","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>In India there has traditionally been little or no tipping, and today tipping is unusual outside of fancier restaurants where up to 10% is appropriate. The fancier restaurants may also levy a service charge of up to 15% apart from government taxes. Some restaurants have also have started placing jars at the cashier for people to drop in some change if they feel so, but this is a rather rare phenomenon. Most clubs in India have a complete ban on its members from tipping. Usually no service industry except the food services industry expects a tip. In India, it is unlawful for taxi or rickshaw drivers to charge anything above the meter.</p>","frontmatter":{"path":"/india","title":"India","author":"Joni","date":"2019-11-22","image":"india.jpg"}},"image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.5001007861318283,"src":"/static/8d75b5a2fa6d86f2fad44a2a79e2ba80/90537/india.jpg","srcSet":"/static/8d75b5a2fa6d86f2fad44a2a79e2ba80/b3ebb/india.jpg 270w,\n/static/8d75b5a2fa6d86f2fad44a2a79e2ba80/95b54/india.jpg 540w,\n/static/8d75b5a2fa6d86f2fad44a2a79e2ba80/90537/india.jpg 1080w,\n/static/8d75b5a2fa6d86f2fad44a2a79e2ba80/3cda3/india.jpg 1620w,\n/static/8d75b5a2fa6d86f2fad44a2a79e2ba80/1f682/india.jpg 2160w,\n/static/8d75b5a2fa6d86f2fad44a2a79e2ba80/6bbaa/india.jpg 7442w","sizes":"(max-width: 1080px) 100vw, 1080px"}}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"image":"india.jpg"}}}